description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Transforming Care Senior Housing Project Officer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;£39,880 - £42,821 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Number of hours: &lt;/strong&gt;37 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Torbay &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: &lt;/strong&gt;18th November 2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: &lt;/strong&gt;27th November 2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new and exciting opportunity for a creative/ solution focussed/ passionate/ forward thinking housing strategist to develop and expand the range of specialist housing options available for people with learning disability and/or autism in Devon. The pandemic has underlined the crucial role of housing and supporting people to live independent, fulfilled lives in a home of their own is at the heart of Transforming Care (TCP). This is a shared priority for the NHS Clinical Commissioning group, Torbay, Plymouth and Devon Local Authorities who are seeking to recruit an individual with the requisite skills and experience to lead on the housing agenda and development across the market to drive change across Devon which results in sustainable housing solutions for individuals in the Transforming Care cohort. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing collaborative and innovate approaches with a range of stakeholders across Devon, including housing developers, investors, providers, RSLs and contractors to increase the range of specialist housing options available in th3e immediate, mid and longer term.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project managing the practical implementation of bespoke solutions as necessitated by individuals in the TCP cohort across Devon.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enabling strong coalitions of relevant stakeholders to promote problem solving and develop good practice at a local level to create a sustainable housing model in the long term. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will cover geographical Devon and will be hosted by Torbay Council. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For information please contact Sue McDermott on 07735415674.&lt;/p&gt;
